[Eating raw shellfish only during months containing an "r" in their name (in English) may carry a lower risk of infection than eating them during the warmer months (May, June, July, and August), but only in the northern hemisphere (it should be reversed below the equator). However, since global warming has occurred, and with the shellfish being shipped quickly from warmer to colder areas, the adage is no longer very helpful.

Successful isolation of _Vibrio parahaemolyticus_ from diarrheic stools must start with consideration of this particular organism, as _Vibrio_ spp. and a number of organisms, including the enteropaths of _Escherichia coli_, require special media to either facilitate growth (_Vibrio_ spp. require higher salinity and are referred to as halophilic) or aid to identification (_E. coli_ O157 can be screened for using its lack of fermentation of sorbitol). - Mod.LL

The state of Florida can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2891152,212. A county map can be seen at http://geology.com/county-map/florida-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
